      • createElement

        public UIElement createElement(UIType uiType,
                               String value)
        A method for element definition with element type and value This method will not instantiate the WebElement or find the HTML element on the page. It will only create the object that defines the expected location of the HTML element on the page. It employs lazy instantiation, so the WebDriver.findElement(By) is not called until it is needed by a method such as UIElement.isPresent() or UIElement.isVisible();
        Parameters:
        uiType - what By method should we use? (For example xpath or CSS)
        value - what is the specification to find the element. For example: //div[contains(text(),'MyCourse')] or div#row1
        Returns:
        a UIElement object that contains the information needed to find the element later.

      • createElement

        A method for element definition with element type, value and 'verify' 'verify' is a flag for verifying the element in method 'verifyAllElements()'. if it's true, the element will be automatically verified in the method. if it's false, the element will be skipped.
